args: I met him back when I was still a kid.\nI lost my parents, and I was passed around\nby relatives until I ended up with the Church.
HE will be the next apostle?\nBut he is yet a child!
Yet he has the makings of an apostle.\nI would ask you look after him for a time.
And why is a dragon of my might being\nasked to play nursemaid to a whelp?
Heh. Yeah, he said that—but he still paid me\nmore mind than any other adult I've yet met.
Let us have stew for dinner this evening.\nThat way, even your hated vegetables\nshould prove palatable.

You can't sleep because you're afraid of
the howling of the wolves? I suppose I'll
allow you to sleep in my bed until you are
used to it.
He taught me so many things, including what\nI needed to know to be an apostle.
Thought is a weapon. Rather than\nhaphazard guessing, use the magic of a\nclear mind and logic to derive answers.
You move well, but you have a century's\nworth of training to go before you are\neven remotely a match for me.
He was a parent. A teacher. A master. And...
Hot beans! Okay, I got out of that tunnel\nsomehow, but have NO idea where I am.
I got the gaolstone out, but...\nHurk! *cough* *hack*
Damn, those rocks messed me up good.\nDon't think I'll be going anywhere...
Looks like I'm a dead man. And since he's\nconnected to me by the Sigil, that means\nhe's going to meet his maker as well.
If you learn anything of use, you must\nreturn to me and report. Understood?
He was right: I've got a lot to learn.\nBut still...
I wanted to be like you...\nAnd I wanted you to acknowledge me...
Yet this is the sad result... Heh.\nWhat an idiot I am.
Honestly. I was quite clear in warning you\nnot to venture too far, was I not?
Ramiel...? Well, this is a weird thing\nto imagine in my final moments...
Still, while you're here, care to say\na couple of nice things about me?
What childish nonsense are you speaking?\nYour wounds are deep, but you'll be fine if\nyou receive suitable care.
Wait, it really IS you?!\nWhat are you doing here?!
You were delayed in returning, so I used\nthe Sigil to track you down.
Now lend me your shoulder.\nThere's a village not far from here.

Nevin, as punishment for breaking your
promise to me, you will be on toilet-
cleaning duty for a week—as well as
shopping duty and bath-cleaning duty.
This is completely justified, dear boy.\nAnd do be sure and reflect on what\nyou've done in the meantime.
The apostle and the archangel work\ntogether to ensure their duty is done.
Please do not try to take on too much all\non your own. Remember that I am your\narchangel until your final day.
...And then your injuries meant we could\nnot go on missions, so the other apostles\nhad to make up for it.
I also received a lecture from Sandalphon\ngoing on and on about our methods.
I said I was sorry! Give it a rest.
I do not think I will. Instead, this tale will\nfind its way to your children, and your\nchildren's children, and so forth.
I have no doubt it will, you lousy angel.

Did I not teach you how to read at some
point? Perhaps you could pick up a book
and learn some new words to call me
when you're sassing... Hmm?
...Sandalphon. She wants us\nto take on an urgent task.
Sadly, we shall have to postpone it.
A hawk's a hawk, a kite's a kite.\nBut if they fly together long enough...
Oh, just mumbling to myself.\nC'mon, let's get this thing in gear.
We've got the Goddess's will to administer.
